<section>
	<h2>Purpose</h2>
	<p>Equalises the height of elements that are on the same baseline.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Use when</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Elements of varying heights are displayed on the same baseline.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Do not use when</h2>
	<p>No known use cases when this plugin should not be used.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Working example</h2>
	<p><a href="../../../demos/eqht-css/eqht-css-en.html">Working example of the equal height pure css plugin</a></p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>How to implement</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Add the class <code>wb-eqht-css</code> to the element that contains the elements for which you want the height to be equal.</li>
		<li>Add the class <code>wb-eqht-grd</code> to the grid that gets the equal height treatment.</li>
		<li>Add the class <code>hght-inhrt</code> to the nested element for which you want the height to be equal.</li>
		<li>Add the class <code>eqht-trgt</code> to the equalize element. Is the same as applying <code>hght-inhrt</code> up to the child of <code>wb-eqht</code>.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

